  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Adiposity is a state of sub-clinical inflammation, thus hepcidin is increased in adiposity,
      often leading to iron deficiency in this population group. Central adiposity is generally
      considered having a greater negative effect on health compared to peripheral adiposity.
      Whether this can be also seen in hepcidin and thereby in iron absorption is uncertain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
